Hong Kong Says 13 Dark Pools in City, Will Monitor Industry

-- B y   L y n n   T h o m a s s o n
-- 
2011-04-06T07:21:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/hong-kong-says-13-dark-pools-in-city-will-monitor-industry.html
Hong Kong ’s government is monitoring
the development of dark pools, said K.C. Chan, Secretary for
Financial Services and the Treasury in a statement to the city’s
legislature.  He said the Treasury bureau and the Securities and Futures
Commission have participated in international discussions on
dark pool regulation. There are 13 dark pools, private platforms
that allow stock trades without displaying bids and offers,
operating in Hong Kong, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lynn Thomasson in Hong Kong at 
 lthomasson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net  